cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment analysis in natural language text, specifically news articles. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment analysis is often used in search engines to improve the relevance of search results. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as sentiment analysis is a common application of machine learning and natural language processing. It may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the testing of different sentiment dictionaries and the performance of different approaches. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the analysis of sentiment in news articles has implications for understanding public opinion and the impact of media on society.
